<h2 style="text-align: left;">
  <span style="font-weight: normal;">DM Etiquette</span>
</h2>
<div><span style="font-weight: normal;">How to DM me</span></div>
<div>
  <span><!--more--></span><span style="font-family: Sometype Mono;"><span style="font-size: 16px;">Modern chat communication should be done in a way that saves time for all
      participants and enables an efficient, asynchronous exchange of
      information.&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 16px;">Don’t expect an answer if you just write “Hello” in DMs</strong><span style="font-size: 16px;">. Don’t call someone out of the blue. Instead, phrase a message that
      allows your chat partners to provide a meaningful response as soon as they
      allocate time to read and answer your message.</span></span>
</div>
<div>
  <span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-family: Sometype Mono;"><br /></span></span>
</div>
<div>
  <span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-family: Sometype Mono;">Part 1.</span></span>
</div>
<div>
  <span style="font-size: 16px;"><span><!--more--></span></span>
</div>
<div>
  <span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-family: Sometype Mono;">Don't just DM me hi and say nothing DM me with good purpose, not random
      stupid stuff unless your my irl friend.</span></span>
</div>
<span></span>
<div><br /></div>
<div>Part 2.</div>
<span><!--more--></span>
<div>Don't DM me out of the blue ping me in the server first :)</div>
<div>Make sure to state your reason of DMing me.</div>
<div><br /></div>
<div>Part 3</div>
<span><!--more--></span>
<div>
  If you wish to VC with me please ping me in the server/DMs first before
  calling me. Likely if you don't ping me before calling me I will probably not
  answer.
</div>
<div><br /></div>
<div><br /></div>
